  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 12:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] Process Management Fixed \u2014 Single Bot Instance Enforced\n\n**Task:** Fix the multi-process zombie bug found in P2 and prevent recurrence.\n\n**Problem:** Killing zombie PIDs created a cascade \u2014 watchdog saw \"pm-bot DEAD\", restarted, spawned more zombies. The `bash -c \"cd ... && source ... && python3 ...\"` screen command created orphan subprocesses.\n\n**Fixes applied:**\n1. **`scripts/start-pm-bot.sh`** \u2014 Clean startup script using `exec` to replace bash with python (no intermediate subshells). Kills any stale trading_bot processes before starting.\n2. **`scripts/bot-watchdog.sh`** \u2014 Zombie killer rewritten to use `pstree` to identify the legitimate screen-owned python PID. Kills only orphan processes.\n3. **All watchdog screen restarts** now use `start-pm-bot.sh` instead of inline `bash -c`.\n\n**Verification:** `pstree` shows clean tree: `screen \u2192 python3 (1 thread)`. No orphans.\n\n**Remaining issue:** Single python process still produces 3x loop cycle log entries (triple-logging). This is an ASYNC bug inside the code (likely 3 concurrent event loop tasks all running the main while-loop). NOT a process issue \u2014 all 3 share the same state, guards, and window_traded flag. Cosmetic for now; the `window_traded` flag prevents actual double trades within a single process.\n\n**Impact:** \n- Zero zombie processes going forward (watchdog prevents them)\n- Clean startup (exec replaces bash)\n- Indicator logging should now work (single process, consistent `_last_indicators`)\n- Next trade will be the definitive test\n\n**Next P3:** Investigate the async triple-logging bug. The `run()` method has only ONE while-loop, but asyncio is executing it 3 times per cycle. May be related to how `binance_feed`/`ob_poller`/`pm_feed` interact with the event loop.\n\n---\n## 2026-03-31 12:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] \ud83d\udc1b CRITICAL BUG FIXED: 3 Bot Processes Running Simultaneously\n\n**Task:** Audit the multi-loop bug causing double trades and broken indicator logging.\n\n**ROOT CAUSE FOUND AND FIXED:**\nThree separate `python3 trading_bot.py` processes were running simultaneously:\n- **PID 3837975** \u2014 zombie from Mar 30, running 577 minutes\n- **PID 3908044** \u2014 zombie from Mar 30, running 504 minutes  \n- **PID 4150498** \u2014 current instance from 10:10 today\n\nThe two zombie processes were left over from previous screen session restarts that didn't properly kill the old Python process. All three were:\n1. **Trading on the same PM account** \u2192 double/triple trades\n2. **Writing to the same log file** \u2192 interleaved log entries\n3. **Writing to the same JSONL** \u2192 race condition on indicator data\n4. **Using the same `_last_indicators`** \u2192 indicators from one process overwritten by another\n\n**This explains ALL previously \"mysterious\" bugs:**\n- \u274c Double-trade bug (Mar 30): 3 bots saw same signal \u2192 3 trades placed\n- \u274c Indicator logging empty: zombie processes had OLD code without indicator capture\n-",
